Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 6. Nxc6 bxc6 {[%csl Gc6] The exchange
on c6 clearly favours Black: the d5-square is not weak anymore, d7-d5 is an
idea to seize further space in the centre and the open b-file can be very
useful sometimes.} 7. Bc4 {The most logical, developing the bishop on an
active diagonal and fighting against the advance of the d-pawn.} (7. Bg5 $6 {
only brings problems for White:} Rb8 8. Rb1 h6 9. Bxf6 ({If} 9. Bh4 $2 {
Black has the strong reply} Qa5 $1 {[%cal Gf6e4,Gf8b4,Gb8b2] when White
