already lacks a decent way of defending the b2-pawn.} 15. O-O-O $2 Bf4+ 16. Kb1
Rb4 {[%csl Rd4]} 17. Bc4 Be5 $19 {and White already faces material losses.}) (
14. O-O-O Bf4+ 15. Kb1 Rb8 16. Bc4 O-O $17 {[%cal Gf8d8] also seems bad for
White.}) {A natural variation now is} 14... Be5 15. Qc4 O-O 16. Be2 Rab8 17.
Qxc6 Rxb2 18. Nd5 Qe6 $1 $17 {when Black definitely has a better game with
