{This is another instructive example of an attack in positions with
opposite-coloured bishops.} 33. Kg2 Qd7 34. g4 $1 Qe8 35. g5 {g5-g6 is a
threat and Black can't defend on f7 anymore.} Qd7 36. gxh6 gxh6 (36... g6 37.
Qxg6+) 37. Qg6+ Kh8 (37... Bg7 38. Rg3 $18) 38. Bxf7 Bg7 39. Bd5 {Pawn is won,
but the attack has not ended yet.} Qd8 40. Rc3 {The idea is Be6 and Rc8.} Re8
41. Rc7 Re7 (41... Qxc7 42. Qxe8+ Kh7 43. Bg8+ Kh8 44. Bf7+ Kh7 45. Bg6#) 42.
Rc6 Bf6 43. Bf7 (43. Qxf6+ $4 Rg7+ {loses a queen}) 43... Bg7 44. Be6 {there
was no defence against Rc8 or Bf5 threats.} 1-0

