Qh6 17. Qd3 $6 e4 $1 18. fxe4 Ne5) 12... f5 13. f3 b6 $146 14. Be3 (14. b4 Ba6
$5 {This nice trick shows why it's important to avoid playing a7-a6 too early}
15. a4 (15. Nc3 Rc8 16. Qb3 Qc7 {[%csl Gc4]}) 15... Bxb5 16. axb5 Bg5 17. Ra6
h5 $132 {with good counterplay on dark squares.}) 14... a6 15. Nc3 Bg5 16. Bf2
(16. Qd2 Bxe3+ 17. Qxe3 Nc5 $132) 16... Qf6 $132 {Black intends to play Qh6 &
Be3 forcing dark-squared bishops exchange. It's not so easy to prevent this as
the idea e5-e4 is in the air too.} *

