) 10... Nd7 (10... O-O 11. O-O f5 12. f4 (12. Bd2 f4 13. a5 Bf5 {Pichot -
Carlsen, chess24.com blitz 2019} 14. Bg4 $5 $14) 12... a6 13. Na3 Nd7 (13... b5
14. axb5 axb5 15. Bxb5 Rxa3 $2 16. Rxa3 Qb6+ 17. Be3 Qxb5 18. Rb3) 14. Nc4 b6
$13 {Nepomniaschy - Carlsen, Abidjan blitz 2019}) 11. O-O (11. b4 $146 a6 12.
Na3 b6) (11. Bd2 Nf6 12. Be3 a6 13. Na3 $2 Qa5+) 11... O-O {This is one of the
critical positions tested in the Caruana-Carlsen match, and here White has a
fairly wide choice.} 12. Bd2 {Now a4-a5 is a kind of positional threat so it's
better to do something about it.} (12. b4 a6 (12... f5 13. a5) 13. Na3 b6 (
13... a5 14. bxa5 Rxa5 15. Nc4 Ra8 16. Be3 f5 17. a5 f4 18. Bb6 Qe8 19. Re1 $1
(19. Ra3 Qg6 20. Bc7 e4 $132 {Caruana - Carlsen, London (10) 2018}) 19... Rf6
20. Bf3 (20. Bg4 $5) 20... Bd8 21. Qb1 Nxb6 22. Nxb6 Bxb6 23. Qxb6 Ra6 24. Qb4
