f4 15. Bf2 Bh4 $36) 14... exf4 15. Bxf4 Nc5 16. Nc4 a5 17. Re1 b6 $13) (12. a5
{This is the key move of White's plan. But playing it right now has a certain
drawback: after 12…a6 the knight has to go not through a3, because after
that the a5-pawn hangs but retreats to c3, where it's placed worse.} a6 13. Nc3
f5 14. Ra3 (14. Bd2 e4 (14... b5 15. axb6 Nxb6 16. Nb1 $1 Rb8 17. Ba5 $14) 15.
