Rb1 Nd7 19. c5 $1 Nxc5 20. Nc4 Ra6 21. a5 $44) 13. Na3 a5 {Weakening the
b5-square, but now we still intend to seriously block the advance of the white
pawns, and it is not easy for White to use it.} (13... b6 $6 14. a5 b5 15. c4
$16) 14. Bb5 (14. Nb5 f5 (14... Nc5 $5 15. c3 Bd7 16. b4 Ne4 17. Be1 axb4 18.
cxb4 Rc8 19. a5 Bg5 $13) 15. f4 (15. b4 axb4 16. Bxb4 Nb8 $1 {Knight goes to
a6 now. Yes, the d6-pawn has to be defended, our pieces are rather passive,
but now White's pawn structure has shattered a bit and we are not so afraid
anymore. The c4-c5 threat is not easy to prepare.} 17. c4 Na6 18. Ba3 Kh8 (
18... b6 $6 19. a5 $1 bxa5 20. c5 $16 Nxc5 21. Bxc5 dxc5 22. d6 $18) 19. a5 e4
$13 {Here, we are not afraid of c4-c5 anymore. After all, with an extra pawn,
