White's pawn structure, does not bring Black much trouble.}) (15. f3 $146 f4 {
[%cal Gf8f6,Gf6h6]} 16. b4 Rf6 17. Bd3 Rh6 $132) 15... Nf6 $1 16. Kh1 (16. Be3
exf4 17. Bxf4 Bd7 $132) 16... Ne4 $132) (14. c3 {the idea is also to prepare
