Bb7 $5 19. Qg3 Kh8 20. Rae1 Qd4 21. Nc2 Qf4 22. f3 Rfd8 23. Be4 Bxe4 24. fxe4
Qxg3 25. hxg3 Bh6 $44) 19. gxf3 Bb7 20. Be4 Bxe4 21. fxe4 Rfc8 22. Rfc1 Bf8 $44
23. Nc2 $5 Rc4 24. Ne3 Rxe4 25. Rc6 Rd8 $132) 18... e4 19. Bxb5 Qxf5 20. Qxf5
Bxf5 21. Bd7 Bxd7 22. Rxd7 Bxb2 23. Nc4 Bg7 $14 {[#] White has a slight edge
thanks to his more active pieces, but this endgame is very drawish, as Carlsen
demonstrated in the following two games:} 24. g3 (24. Rfd1 Rac8 25. Ne3 Rc5 26.
g4 (26. g3 $5 Bh6 27. Nd5 Kg7) 26... Ra5 27. R1d2 (27. Re7 Rxa2 28. Rxe4 a5
$132) 27... Bh6 28. Re7 Bxe3 29. fxe3 Rg5 30. Rxe4 f5 $11 {1/2-1/2 (73) Xiong,
J (2709)-Carlsen,M (2863) Lichess.org INT 2020}) 24... Rfd8 25. Rfd1 Rxd7 26.
Rxd7 Rc8 27. Nd6 Rc1+ 28. Kg2 Rc2 29. Nxe4 Rxa2 30. Rd8+ Bf8 31. Nf6+ Kg7 32.
Nh5+ Kg8 33. g4 a5 $132 34. g5 a4 35. h4 Rb2 36. Nf6+ Kg7 37. h5 Rb5 38. f4 h6
39. Ng4 Ba3 40. Nxh6 Be7 41. Rd7 Bxg5 42. Nxf7 Rb2+ 43. Kf3 Bxf4 44. Ne5+ Kh6
45. Kxf4 a3 46. Rd5 Rb4+ 47. Kg3 a2 48. Ra5 a1=Q 49. Rxa1 Kxh5 50. Ra5 Rb1 51.
Kf4 Rf1+ 52. Nf3+ 1/2-1/2

