1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 e5 6. Ndb5 d6 7. Bg5 a6 8.
Na3 b5 9. Bxf6 gxf6 10. Nd5 Bg7 11. g3 $5 {[#]} Ne7 $1 {We can take the
independent path here, too.} (11... f5 12. Bg2 (12. exf5 Bxf5 13. Bg2 Be6 14.
c3 O-O 15. Nc2 {is another typical Sveshnikov middlegame.}) 12... fxe4 13. Bxe4
Be6 {is the main line}) 12. Nxe7 (12. Bg2 Nxd5 13. Qxd5 Be6 14. Qd3 (14. Qc6+
Ke7 15. Qb7+ Qd7 16. Qxd7+ Kxd7 17. c3 Bh6 $1 18. Nc2 a5 19. a3 Bb3 20. Ne3
Bxe3 21. fxe3 Ke7 $15) (14. Qd2 h5 $1 15. O-O (15. h4 Qb6 16. O-O b4 17. Nb1
Bh6 $15) 15... h4 16. Rfd1 Ke7 $13) 14... Qd7 {[%csl Yd6][%cal Gf6f5,Ga8d8]}
15. O-O O-O 16. Rfd1 Rad8 17. c4 f5 $13) 12... Qxe7 13. Bg2 {[#] With the
bishop on g2, we cannot play 13...f5 like we did in the previous lines.
However, we have another idea.} d5 $1 {The big point. Black gets promising
play with this pawn sacrifice.} 14. Qxd5 (14. exd5 $6 {is very suspicious due
to} Qb4+ 15. c3 Qxb2 {Black seems to be winning, but White still has an ace up
his sleeve} 16. Qb3 $1 (16. Nc2 Qxc3+ 17. Kf1 {1-0 (24) Sjugirov,S (2663)
-Paravyan,D (2647) Lichess.org INT 2021} Bh6 $19) 16... Qxa1+ (16... Qxb3 17.
axb3 Rb8 18. O-O f5 19. c4 bxc4 20. Nxc4 e4 21. Ra5 O-O $11) 17. Ke2 Bg4+ 18.
f3 Qxh1 19. Bxh1 Bd7 20. Qb4 Rc8 $13 {[%cal Gh7h4,Gg7f8,Gf6f5,Yh8h6]}) (14. c3
dxe4 15. Bxe4 Rb8 16. Nc2 f5 17. Bc6+ Kf8 18. Qh5 Rb6 19. Bd5 {1-0 (58)
Malicka,M (2329)-Kavutskiy,K (2395) San Jose 2022} Bh6 $1 $15 {[%cal Gf8g7,
Re1c1,Yb6g6]}) 14... Bb7 $6 {[%csl Rb7] The bishop is misplaced here.} (14...
Rb8 $1 $146 {[%csl Ye6][%cal Gc8e6] Black should aim for Be6. Moreover, the
rook is placed well on b8.} 15. O-O (15. Qc6+ Bd7 16. Qxa6 Qb4+ 17. c3 Qxb2 18.
O-O O-O $44) 15... O-O $44 {[%csl Ra3] It will take White a while to bring his
knight into the game. In the meantime, Black will carry out ...f5 and open the
center for his bishop pair.} 16. Qd3 {[#]} (16. c3 $2 Rd8 17. Qb3 Be6 18. Qc2
b4 $17) 16... f5 $1 17. c3 (17. exf5 e4 18. Qb3 Bxf5 19. c3 b4 $15) 17... fxe4
18. Qxe4 f5 19. Qe2 Kh8 $44 20. Nc2 f4 $1 21. Be4 Rb6 $1 $132 {[%cal Gb6h6,
Ge7g5]}) (14... Qb4+ {doesn't work now in the view of} 15. c3 Qxb2 16. O-O $18
{[%csl Ra8]}) 15. Qd2 Rd8 16. Qe2 f5 17. O-O fxe4 18. Bxe4 Bxe4 19. Qxe4 O-O
20. Rad1 $16 {[#] Black has no compensation for the pawn.} Qe6 21. c4 f5 22.
Qe2 Rxd1 23. Rxd1 e4 24. cxb5 axb5 25. Qxb5 f4 26. Qc4 Qf7 27. Qxf7+ Rxf7 28.
Nc4 Ra7 29. Rd8+ Kf7 30. Nd6+ Ke7 31. Nc8+ Kxd8 32. Nxa7 fxg3 33. hxg3 Bxb2 34.
Nc6+ Kd7 35. Nb4 Kd6 36. Nc2 Kc5 37. Kf1 Bc1 38. Ke2 Kc4 39. Ne3+ Kb4 40. Ng4
Ka3 41. Nf6 e3 42. fxe3 h6 43. Ng4 h5 44. Nf6 Kxa2 45. Nxh5 Kb3 46. Nf4 Kc4 47.
Nd3 Kd5 48. Nxc1 Ke4 49. Nd3 Kf5 50. Nf2 Kg5 51. Kf3 Kf5 52. e4+ Kg5 53. g4 Kf6
54. Kf4 Kg6 55. g5 Kf7 56. Ng4 Kg6 57. e5 Kf7 58. Kf5 Kg7 59. g6 Kg8 60. Kg5
Kf8 61. Nh6 Kg7 62. e6 Kf8 63. Kf6 Ke8 64. g7 Kd8 65. g8=Q+ Kc7 66. Qe8 Kb6 67.
Qd7 Ka5 68. e7 Kb4 69. e8=Q Kb3 70. Qee6+ 1-0

